	* configure.ac (AC_INIT): Bumped version to 1.0.10.

	* db.c (cmeDBCreateOpen, cmeDBOpen): Enable WAL journal mode,
	synchronous=NORMAL, and 8 MB page cache (PRAGMA cache_size=-8000)
	on every database open, allowing concurrent readers, removing the
	double-fsync overhead of the default DELETE journal, and keeping
	hot pages in memory.

	* db.c (cmeMemTableToMemDB): Replace O(n²) cmeStrConstrAppend
	batch-INSERT loop with an exponential-growth buffer managed by the
	SQL_ENSURE macro, reducing insert time from quadratic to O(n log n)
	amortized.

	* db.c (cmeSQLRows): Use exponential realloc doubling for the
	result-row array instead of a fixed pre-allocation, then trim to
	exact size at the end; eliminates over-allocation for small result
	sets and re-allocation for large ones.

	* db.c (cmeResultMemTableClean): Add NULL guard on the outer array
	and cache the element pointer before memset to avoid computing
	strlen twice per element.

	* db.c, engine_interface.c, engine_admin.c: Remove deprecated
	PRAGMA empty_result_callbacks = ON from all five call sites;
	sqlite3_get_table already returns column names for empty tables
	without it.

