	* configure.ac (AC_INIT): Bumped version to 1.0.7.

	* configure.ac: Added --with-max-threads=N option (default 4).
	Defines CDSE_MAX_THREADS which controls the libmicrohttpd worker
	thread pool size and the connection limit at build time.

	* common.h: Added #include <pthread.h>.  Added cmeDefaultMaxThreads
	and cmeDefaultMaxConnections macros.  Changed cmeResultMemTable,
	cmeResultMemTableRows, cmeResultMemTableCols from plain extern to
	extern __thread (GCC thread-local storage) so each worker thread
	owns an independent result buffer.  Added extern declarations for
	cmePerlMutex and cmePowerMutex.

	* main.c: Changed the three cmeResultMemTable globals to __thread.
	Added definitions of cmePerlMutex and cmePowerMutex, both
	initialised to PTHREAD_MUTEX_INITIALIZER.

	* engine_admin.h, engine_admin.c: Added numThreads parameter to
	cmeWebServiceSetup().  Both MHD_start_daemon() calls (HTTP and
	HTTPS) now use MHD_USE_INTERNAL_POLLING_THREAD with
	MHD_OPTION_THREAD_POOL_SIZE and MHD_OPTION_CONNECTION_LIMIT,
	enabling a bounded worker-thread pool.  cmeWebServiceStart() passes
	numThreads=0 (uses cmeDefaultMaxThreads).

	* webservice_interface.h: Added connectionStartTime (time_t) and
	requestDataSize (long int) fields to cmeWebServiceConnectionInfoStruct
	so per-connection timing and upload-size tracking is no longer held
	in thread-unsafe static local variables.

	* webservice_interface.c: Removed static local connectionStartTime
	and requestDataSize from cmeWebServiceAnswerConnection(); replaced
	with con_info->connectionStartTime and con_info->requestDataSize.
	Promoted powerStatus from a static local inside
	cmeWebServiceProcessRequest() to a file-scope static
	cmeEnginePowerStatus, read under cmePowerMutex at request entry
	and written through cmePowerMutex in the engineCommands handler.
	cmeWebServiceProcessParserScriptResource() now acquires
	cmePerlMutex at entry (via lock before work begins) and releases
	it in the cmeWebServiceProcessParserScriptResourceFree() macro
	that precedes every return, serialising concurrent access to the
	shared Perl interpreter.

	* function_tests.c, function_tests.h: Added testThreadSafety()
	which spawns cmeDefaultMaxThreads POSIX threads; each thread opens
	an independent SQLite database, inserts 10 rows, queries them back,
	and verifies the results using the thread-local cmeResultMemTable.
	Called automatically from testEngMgmnt().

	* README: Updated version to 1.0.7; revised section II to document
	the new multithreading engine; revised section IV layer 7 to
	reflect that concurrent multi-user support is now available.

2026-03-26 Omar A. Herrera Reyna <0h3rr3r4@gmail.com>

	* configure.ac (AC_INIT): Bumped version to 1.0.6.

	* README: Updated version to 1.0.6 and documented the ECDSA P-384
	certificate update and the expanded gen_test_certs.sh algorithm menu.

	* TEST/testCertAuth/gen_test_certs.sh: Extended to support 7
	algorithm presets selectable via --algo / -a flag:
	  rsa2048  (RSA 2048-bit + SHA-256)
	  rsa4096  (RSA 4096-bit + SHA-256)
	  ecp256   (ECDSA P-256  + SHA-256)
	  ecp384   (ECDSA P-384  + SHA-384, new default)
	  ecp521   (ECDSA P-521  + SHA-512)
	  ed25519  (Ed25519, intrinsic hash, TLS 1.3+)
	  ed448    (Ed448,   intrinsic hash, TLS 1.3+)
	The script now uses 'openssl genpkey' uniformly for all key types.
	X.509 keyUsage is set correctly per key family: RSA gets
	keyEncipherment in addition to digitalSignature; EC/EdDSA get
	digitalSignature only (key agreement is handled by ephemeral ECDH).
	Added named flags --algo / --output-dir / --server-cn alongside the
	existing positional arguments (backward compatible).
	Certificate summary now shows the full signature algorithm string.

	* TEST/testCertAuth/openssl.cnf: Removed keyEncipherment from
	web_cert, usr_cert, and v3_req sections; replaced with
	digitalSignature only (compatible with both RSA/ECDHE and EC/EdDSA).
	Added explanatory comments for RSA-specific keyEncipherment.

	* TEST/testCertAuth/ca.pem, server.key, server.pem, engineOrg.key,
	engineOrg.pem, engineAdmin.key, engineAdmin.pem, engineAdmin.p12,
	caChain.pem: Regenerated with ECDSA P-384 / SHA-384 (previously
	RSA 4096-bit / SHA-256).  TLS 1.3 negotiates TLS_AES_256_GCM_SHA384.
	Handshake time ~30ms vs ~71ms for RSA 4096 on the same hardware.

